♪In either way♪

12
00:01:22,021 --> 00:01:23,973
♪Tears and fears, happiness♪

13
00:01:24,069 --> 00:01:28,096
♪They are all part of the journey♪

14
00:01:30,547 --> 00:01:34,612
=Double Happiness=

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,995
=Episode 26=

16
00:01:38,316 --> 00:01:39,555
What's the situation?

17
00:01:39,635 --> 00:01:40,956
Has Ms. Lin made any changes?

18
00:01:41,195 --> 00:01:42,555
Yes, of course there are changes.

19
00:01:43,555 --> 00:01:44,876
Don't mess with me.

20
00:01:44,956 --> 00:01:46,236
Every now and then,

21
00:01:46,316 --> 00:01:47,395
Ms. Lin keeps pestering me

22
00:01:47,475 --> 00:01:48,596
asking if you're okay,

23
00:01:48,676 --> 00:01:50,157
how things are going,

24
00:01:50,237 --> 00:01:51,195
or if you'll back out.

25
00:01:51,275 --> 00:01:52,675
If it doesn't work,

26
00:01:52,755 --> 00:01:53,915
we can loosen the conditions.

27
00:01:54,076 --> 00:01:55,236
Negotiation, right?

28
00:01:55,316 --> 00:01:56,077
If it won't do,

29
00:01:56,157 --> 00:01:57,316
we can discuss it again.

30
00:01:57,635 --> 00:01:58,915
You really scared me.

31
00:01:59,475 --> 00:02:00,876
Please pass this on for me,

32
00:02:01,076 --> 00:02:02,675
I'll try to handle it

33
00:02:02,755 --> 00:02:03,716
within half a month.

34
00:02:03,796 --> 00:02:04,517
What I want is

35
00:02:04,597 --> 00:02:06,035
not to throw away

36
00:02:06,115 --> 00:02:07,516
the bonus I should get.

37
00:02:07,915 --> 00:02:08,915
Conditions are the same.

38
00:02:09,156 --> 00:02:10,555
I, for one, can forgo a raise,

39
00:02:10,635 --> 00:02:11,916
but the team I'm leading,

40
00:02:11,996 --> 00:02:13,355
especially the key members,

41
00:02:13,596 --> 00:02:14,915
can't have a reduction.

42
00:02:15,276 --> 00:02:16,716
You can set a threshold,

43
00:02:17,036 --> 00:02:17,637
right?

44
00:02:17,717 --> 00:02:19,115
For this annual bonus,

45
00:02:19,195 --> 00:02:20,516
if you want to earn more,

46
00:02:20,596 --> 00:02:21,916
then increase the reward ratio

47
00:02:21,996 --> 00:02:23,276
a bit for me.

48
00:02:23,635 --> 00:02:24,716
That's not a problem.

49
00:02:24,836 --> 00:02:26,475
I promise you on Ms. Lin's behalf.

50
00:02:26,755 --> 00:02:27,517
Have you been

51
00:02:27,597 --> 00:02:29,116
busy out of your mind lately?

52
00:02:29,276 --> 00:02:29,957
Although

53
00:02:30,037 --> 00:02:32,596
there's a lot going on
and it's quite chaotic,

54
00:02:33,116 --> 00:02:34,955
it's still okay, it feels pretty good.

55
00:02:35,436 --> 00:02:36,036
Listen.

56
00:02:36,116 --> 00:02:36,995
You be careful.

57
00:02:37,075 --> 00:02:37,676
Your manager

58
00:02:37,756 --> 00:02:39,276
isn't an easy one to deal with.

59
00:02:39,635 --> 00:02:40,636
I heard she recently

60
00:02:40,716 --> 00:02:41,436
snapped.

61
00:02:41,516 --> 00:02:42,555
Running around everywhere,

62
00:02:42,635 --> 00:02:43,795
uniting many people,

63
00:02:44,116 --> 00:02:45,876
just to steal your business secretly.

64
00:02:46,596 --> 00:02:47,915
Anyway, be extra careful.

65
00:02:48,755 --> 00:02:50,275
All right, I don't want this either.

66
00:02:50,355 --> 00:02:51,716
After all, she's my mentor.

67
00:02:51,836 --> 00:02:53,876
She has indeed sincerely helped me.

68
00:02:55,036 --> 00:02:56,076
Go ahead with your work.

69
00:02:56,156 --> 00:02:57,316
I still need to organize

70
00:02:57,396 --> 00:02:58,915
this plan.

71
00:02:59,036 --> 00:02:59,995
After my joining,

72
00:03:00,075 --> 00:03:00,995
I'd deliver results.

73
00:03:01,075 --> 00:03:02,556
- Bye bye.
- Bye.

74
00:03:13,475 --> 00:03:14,115
Hello, Ms. Li.

75
00:03:14,195 --> 00:03:15,195
Hello.

76
00:03:34,675 --> 00:03:35,197
You,

77
00:03:35,277 --> 00:03:37,036
don't lose your temper with me here.

78
00:03:37,116 --> 00:03:38,316
Instruction comes from above.

79
00:03:38,556 --> 00:03:39,316
My uncle's idea.

80
00:03:39,396 --> 00:03:40,275
What can I do?

81
00:03:40,355 --> 00:03:41,036
Besides,

82
00:03:41,116 --> 00:03:41,917
this bonus itself

83
00:03:41,997 --> 00:03:42,995
and the compensation

84
00:03:43,075 --> 00:03:44,355
are already hard to agree upon.

85
00:03:44,675 --> 00:03:45,875
Mei Chengyi isn't a fool.

86
00:03:45,955 --> 00:03:46,596
So, how could he

87
00:03:46,676 --> 00:03:48,115
sign the non-compete clause?

88
00:03:48,195 --> 00:03:49,475
You're still too green,

89
00:03:49,596 --> 00:03:50,595
too inexperienced.

90
00:03:50,675 --> 00:03:52,195
You're asking too much, aren't you?

91
00:03:52,355 --> 00:03:54,317
Now you guys
are the ones making trouble, right?

92
00:03:54,397 --> 00:03:55,715
I've tried hard to make amends.

93
00:03:55,795 --> 00:03:56,916
I've used

94
00:03:56,996 --> 00:03:57,797
all my connections

95
00:03:57,877 --> 00:03:59,355
to secure the subsequent orders.

96
00:03:59,515 --> 00:04:00,197
Let me tell you,

97
00:04:00,277 --> 00:04:02,116
within half a year,
as long as Mei Chengyi is

98
00:04:02,235 --> 00:04:03,476
restricted by the clause

99
00:04:03,556 --> 00:04:04,356
and does nothing,

100
00:04:04,436 --> 00:04:06,276
our orders won't disappear.

101
00:04:07,836 --> 00:04:08,517
You're increasing

102
00:04:08,597 --> 00:04:09,715
my workload.

103
00:04:09,795 --> 00:04:11,075
I need to submit a report.

104
00:04:11,475 --> 00:04:12,716
Of course, it would be in vain.

105
00:04:13,156 --> 00:04:14,435
The non-compete compensation

106
00:04:14,515 --> 00:04:15,476
is not a small amount.

107
00:04:15,556 --> 00:04:16,275
Not sure if Uncle

108
00:04:16,355 --> 00:04:17,355
will part with that.

109
00:04:18,315 --> 00:04:18,996
He won't part

110
00:04:19,076 --> 00:04:20,035
with this and that.

111
00:04:20,115 --> 00:04:20,716
So, why not

112
00:04:20,796 --> 00:04:21,875
fire me too?

113
00:04:26,396 --> 00:04:27,197
What?

114
00:04:27,277 --> 00:04:28,716
Nothing.

115
00:04:29,795 --> 00:04:30,995
Seriously.

116
00:05:03,115 --> 00:05:04,115
Li Xiaoxiao.

117
00:05:04,475 --> 00:05:05,915
Don't keep scaring me

118
00:05:05,995 --> 00:05:07,756
like this, okay?

119
00:05:10,115 --> 00:05:11,435
I'm napping well.

120
00:05:12,516 --> 00:05:13,197
What?

121
00:05:13,277 --> 00:05:15,196
I just pushed you a bit.

122
00:05:15,315 --> 00:05:16,395
Not working this morning,

123
00:05:16,475 --> 00:05:17,316
and coming here

124
00:05:17,396 --> 00:05:18,396
to disturb me.

125
00:05:21,636 --> 00:05:22,236
It's not

126
00:05:22,316 --> 00:05:23,836
whether you belong to me or not.

127
00:05:24,475 --> 00:05:26,355
It's that I no longer belong to you.

128
00:05:26,675 --> 00:05:27,517
Where did you go?

129
00:05:27,597 --> 00:05:28,795
How do you not belong to me?

130
00:05:29,756 --> 00:05:30,756
Kaixin.

131
00:05:31,115 --> 00:05:32,436
I had a momentary lapse.

132
00:05:32,516 --> 00:05:33,516
I

133
00:05:34,555 --> 00:05:35,555
got married.

134
00:05:37,756 --> 00:05:39,076
(Marriage Certificate)
He transferred all the money to me.

135
00:05:39,156 --> 00:05:40,596
He even noted 'voluntary gift.'

136
00:05:40,875 --> 00:05:42,036
The house is also notarized.

137
00:05:42,188 --> 00:05:44,224
(Property Ownership Certificate)

138
00:05:45,355 --> 00:05:47,156
Don't laugh anymore.

139
00:05:47,795 --> 00:05:48,956
You just told me

140
00:05:49,036 --> 00:05:50,155
that middle-aged women

141
00:05:50,235 --> 00:05:51,556
shouldn't be led by love.

142
00:05:51,636 --> 00:05:53,116
But then I impulsively

143
00:05:53,196 --> 00:05:54,636
made a love-related mistake.

144
00:05:55,276 --> 00:05:56,675
Kaixin, go ahead and scold me.

145
00:05:57,276 --> 00:05:58,956
Why should I scold you?

146
00:05:59,315 --> 00:06:00,315
I told you

147
00:06:00,516 --> 00:06:02,076
that you shouldn't be led.

148
00:06:02,156 --> 00:06:02,757
But I didn't

149
00:06:02,837 --> 00:06:04,795
say that Song Ran couldn't be led.

150
00:06:05,795 --> 00:06:08,355
(Property Ownership Certificate)
Now he has fallen in love.

151
00:06:09,315 --> 00:06:11,636
Now he cannot extricate himself.

152
00:06:12,315 --> 00:06:14,756
Now you've become a rich woman.

153
00:06:15,836 --> 00:06:16,836
Rich woman.

154
00:06:17,396 --> 00:06:18,795
How about supporting me?

155
00:06:19,636 --> 00:06:20,836
Xu Kaixin.

156
00:06:30,115 --> 00:06:31,115
Hello.

157
00:06:32,276 --> 00:06:32,836
Hello.

158
00:06:32,916 --> 00:06:34,035
I am...

159
00:06:34,115 --> 00:06:35,435
I know.

160
00:06:35,516 --> 00:06:37,155
It's just that our two families

161
00:06:37,235 --> 00:06:39,557
- have complicated relationships.
- Right.

162
00:06:39,637 --> 00:06:41,196
I don't know how to address you.

163
00:06:41,956 --> 00:06:43,435
Call me Mr. You.

164
00:06:43,716 --> 00:06:44,715
My surname is You.

165
00:06:44,795 --> 00:06:45,795
Alright.

166
00:06:46,156 --> 00:06:46,916
We're kind of

167
00:06:46,996 --> 00:06:48,076
in-laws.

168
00:06:48,156 --> 00:06:50,435
- Yes.
- I just wanted to come over and check

169
00:06:50,516 --> 00:06:51,315
if there's anything

170
00:06:51,396 --> 00:06:53,036
I can help with.

171
00:06:53,396 --> 00:06:54,197
No need.

172
00:06:54,277 --> 00:06:55,516
It's all bunch of stuff.

173
00:06:55,596 --> 00:06:57,156
I'll handle it myself.

174
00:06:57,795 --> 00:07:00,596
It's just the kitchen light bulb broke.

175
00:07:01,675 --> 00:07:03,035
When Mei comes around,

176
00:07:03,115 --> 00:07:04,316
I'll ask him to fix it.

177
00:07:04,396 --> 00:07:05,677
No need, why need

178
00:07:05,757 --> 00:07:07,596
Chengyi for this?

179
00:07:07,875 --> 00:07:08,876
Leave it to me.

180
00:07:08,956 --> 00:07:09,956
You'll do it?

181
00:07:10,355 --> 00:07:11,396
Is it okay?

182
00:07:11,716 --> 00:07:12,836
Do you have a stool?

183
00:07:12,995 --> 00:07:13,636
Yes, I do.

184
00:07:13,716 --> 00:07:14,516
This will work.

185
00:07:14,596 --> 00:07:15,437
At our age,

186
00:07:15,517 --> 00:07:16,756
we can't push our limits.

187
00:07:16,836 --> 00:07:18,275
It's not a big deal.

188
00:07:18,355 --> 00:07:19,196
As men,

189
00:07:19,276 --> 00:07:19,997
we handle things

190
00:07:20,077 --> 00:07:21,595
like this at home.

191
00:07:21,675 --> 00:07:22,835
Yes, that's true.

192
00:07:22,915 --> 00:07:23,596
Leave it to me.

193
00:07:23,676 --> 00:07:25,276
Be careful then.

194
00:07:25,555 --> 00:07:26,636
Leave it to me.

195
00:07:27,875 --> 00:07:29,956
Can you do it?

196
00:07:30,036 --> 00:07:30,795
Yes.

197
00:07:30,875 --> 00:07:32,235
You're going up just like that?

198
00:07:32,315 --> 00:07:33,355
Careful.

199
00:07:35,956 --> 00:07:37,555
Wait, wait.

200
00:07:38,115 --> 00:07:39,435
I'll turn off the lights.

201
00:07:39,716 --> 00:07:40,716
Okay.

202
00:07:49,516 --> 00:07:51,596
It's not the light that's broken,

203
00:07:52,396 --> 00:07:54,516
it's this wire that's come loose.

204
00:07:54,716 --> 00:07:56,235
I'll just connect it back.

205
00:07:57,756 --> 00:07:59,675
Do you have tape here?

206
00:07:59,875 --> 00:08:00,437
Yes, I do.

207
00:08:00,517 --> 00:08:01,956
Wait a moment, I'll go find it.

208
00:08:05,836 --> 00:08:06,836
Lili.

209
00:08:08,196 --> 00:08:09,836
I see you just moved in.

210
00:08:10,076 --> 00:08:10,877
I'll see if I can

211
00:08:10,957 --> 00:08:11,915
be of any help.

212
00:08:11,995 --> 00:08:14,756
You and Mr. You really think alike.

213
00:08:15,756 --> 00:08:16,756
What do you mean?

214
00:08:17,795 --> 00:08:18,795
Look.

215
00:08:23,235 --> 00:08:24,235
Dad.

216
00:08:24,956 --> 00:08:26,036
Why are you here?

217
00:08:49,715 --> 00:08:51,795
Can this home manage without me?

218
00:08:54,675 --> 00:08:55,795
Dad, slow down.

219
00:08:56,276 --> 00:08:57,595
Can you handle this?

220
00:09:01,996 --> 00:09:03,075
Okay.

221
00:09:03,996 --> 00:09:04,996
You can do it.

222
00:09:08,435 --> 00:09:09,157
Lili.

223
00:09:09,237 --> 00:09:10,235
Do you need any help?

224
00:09:10,315 --> 00:09:11,396
Nope.

225
00:09:11,996 --> 00:09:13,435
No need, I can do it myself.

226
00:09:14,476 --> 00:09:15,076
Okay, fine.

227
00:09:15,156 --> 00:09:16,156
Where is Kaixin?

228
00:09:16,715 --> 00:09:17,715
In the room.

229
00:09:19,435 --> 00:09:20,276
I'll go take a look.

230
00:09:20,356 --> 00:09:21,356
Okay.

231
00:09:22,595 --> 00:09:23,355
Where are

232
00:09:23,435 --> 00:09:24,355
your principles?

233
00:09:24,435 --> 00:09:25,196
You've changed.

234
00:09:25,276 --> 00:09:26,115
You're changing

235
00:09:26,195 --> 00:09:26,917
like a chameleon.

236
00:09:26,997 --> 00:09:28,996
This is the essence of my life.

237
00:09:29,315 --> 00:09:30,755
Adapt to changes with changes.

238
00:09:30,835 --> 00:09:31,796
Always pursue

239
00:09:31,876 --> 00:09:33,396
your inner needs.

240
00:09:34,036 --> 00:09:34,835
Woman,

241
00:09:34,996 --> 00:09:37,276
you have finally learned my essence.

242
00:09:37,356 --> 00:09:38,037
Congratulations.

243
00:09:38,117 --> 00:09:39,996
Life has started a new journey.

244
00:09:40,236 --> 00:09:41,555
It's so exciting.

245
00:09:47,156 --> 00:09:48,675
What you said is true?

246
00:09:49,595 --> 00:09:51,276
Really, it can't be fake at all.

247
00:09:52,756 --> 00:09:53,356
No.

248
00:09:53,436 --> 00:09:54,996
Then if I can't get along

249
00:09:55,595 --> 00:09:56,235
with Song Ran,

250
00:09:56,315 --> 00:09:57,036
and get a divorce?

251
00:09:57,116 --> 00:09:57,836
You're married.

252
00:09:57,916 --> 00:09:59,156
Why think about these things?

253
00:09:59,955 --> 00:10:00,916
There's no

254
00:10:00,996 --> 00:10:01,596
right answer

255
00:10:01,676 --> 00:10:02,995
for life.

256
00:10:03,075 --> 00:10:04,235
Even if you can rewind,

257
00:10:04,315 --> 00:10:05,676
and you return to that point,

258
00:10:05,756 --> 00:10:06,916
make the opposite decision,

259
00:10:06,996 --> 00:10:07,516
can you

260
00:10:07,596 --> 00:10:08,835
guarantee you'll be happy?

261
00:10:11,835 --> 00:10:13,156
Why don't you go in?

262
00:10:14,715 --> 00:10:16,075
Life is just like this,

263
00:10:16,195 --> 00:10:17,676
choosing the best among the worst.

264
00:10:17,756 --> 00:10:19,235
In the infinite unhappiness,

265
00:10:19,315 --> 00:10:20,875
pick out the limited happiness.

266
00:10:20,955 --> 00:10:22,756
Let's enlarge it.

267
00:10:23,516 --> 00:10:24,516
Do you understand?

268
00:10:26,075 --> 00:10:26,677
Understood.

269
00:10:26,757 --> 00:10:27,755
Kaixin's mind

270
00:10:27,835 --> 00:10:29,036
is full of ideas.

271
00:10:29,116 --> 00:10:30,555
No one can outtalk her.

272
00:10:30,756 --> 00:10:32,396
We should give her a nickname.

273
00:10:32,476 --> 00:10:33,595
Call her 'Always Right'.

274
00:10:34,236 --> 00:10:36,396
Growing wildly day by day.

275
00:10:37,236 --> 00:10:38,396
Endless energy.

276
00:10:39,116 --> 00:10:41,555
However, she's tough-talking
but soft-hearted.

277
00:10:41,756 --> 00:10:42,955
She's a good kid.

278
00:10:43,756 --> 00:10:44,756
Mei.

279
00:10:45,715 --> 00:10:47,156
I hope

280
00:10:47,795 --> 00:10:49,675
even if you don't get married,

281
00:10:49,955 --> 00:10:51,595
you must treat her well.

282
00:10:53,156 --> 00:10:54,156
You're right.

283
00:10:54,435 --> 00:10:55,835
Kaixin is really good.

284
00:10:56,396 --> 00:10:56,996
Besides,

285
00:10:57,076 --> 00:10:58,515
we're not that young anymore.

286
00:10:58,595 --> 00:11:00,636
We're serious about every step we take.

287
00:11:01,795 --> 00:11:02,835
No use saying more.

288
00:11:02,915 --> 00:11:03,996
Just look at how I behave.

289
00:11:04,435 --> 00:11:05,235
Alright.

290
00:11:05,315 --> 00:11:06,475
As for their chatting,

291
00:11:06,555 --> 00:11:07,635
it'll take quite a while.

292
00:11:07,715 --> 00:11:09,835
Why don't you sit
